21/05/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Albanian and US army forces launched a joint military exercise Tuesday (20 May) in the town of Durres on the Adriatic Sea.
The exercise will continue for two weeks and is part of US efforts to help Albania's army achieve NATO standards.
The exercise aims to test the ability of Albanian units to cope with humanitarian crises and other emergency situations.
(Albanian Daily News - 21/05/03;
ATA, Beta - 20/05/03)
